      "writtenOn": "2018-05-08T15:30:25Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Not sure if it would make things easier, but it seems like using the \"flatten\" option described at https://godoc.org/cloud.google.com/go/datastore might make things easier. E.g.:\n\ntype OneTestDigestExp struct {\n  Name   string\n  Digest string\n  Label  string\n}\n\ntype TestDigestExp struct {\n  Key  *datastore.Key `datastore:\"__key__\"`\n  List []OneTestDigestExp `datastore:\",flatten\"`\n}\n\nThat would be equivalent to something like:\ntype TestDigestExp struct {\n  Key    *datastore.Key `datastore:\"__key__\"`\n  Name   []string       `datastore:\"List.Name\"`\n  Digest []string       `datastore:\"List.Digest\"`\n  Label  []string       `datastore:\"List.Label\"`\n}",
      "revId": "8d58f9fca4ac72850f01e6469717a153c502066a",
