    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "3d31b314_ffef1eb3",
        "filename": "golden/go/expstorage/exps_types.go",
        "patchSetId": 37
      },
      "lineNbr": 115,
      "author": {
        "id": 5620
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-05-09T18:48:16Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Yes, I am assuming that the time the iteration takes is still negligible compared to the time it takes to fetch them from the db over the network. The point of this is to keep the expectations minimal, we don\u0027t want duplicate entries and assigning \"untriaged\" to an entry is identical to removing them. \nIn that case the empty slot will be filled by something else. \nI think it\u0027s imperative to avoid any fragmentation to keep the number of TDESlice instances necessary to store expectations to a minimum.",
      "parentUuid": "42ebabb6_293ff7c3",
      "revId": "8d58f9fca4ac72850f01e6469717a153c502066a",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
