      "message": "nit: It probably doesn\u0027t matter that much, but it might be better to always increment c.revision before calling RunInTransaction. Same for Update and Delete below.\n\n(Unless you store \"revision\" in the DB, there is no way to avoid a race condition between updating ignores and incrementing c.revision. The docs for Revision() seem to indicate it would be better for Revision to increment when there is no change rather than not increment when there is a change, so IMO it\u0027s better to increment before modifying the DB.)",
